              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Several ion implanted silicon detectors were placed at",
                "laboratory angles of 110-170 degrees. At energies below",
                " 2.7 MeV three detectors (25 mm**2,100 mum) and at",
                "higher energies two (25 mm**2,300 mum) detectors were",
                "used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The helium targets were prepared by implanting 60-KeV",
                " He-4 ions in 1.50-mum thick tantalum foils. The",
                "resulting helium depth distribution has a mean range of",
                " 180 nm and a width of 85 nm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MOMIX"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": 6.0,
                "maximum_value": 7.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainties in the cross",
                "section values, increase from 6% at the low energy",
                "and to 7% at the high energy end. These uncertainties",
                "result from statistical errors and background",
                "subtraction uncertainties in the helium peak area",
                "determination and from the uncertainty in the helium",
                "content. When comparing the cross sections taken at",
                "different energies these relative values are more",
                "accurate with an estimated inaccuracy below 3%."
              ]
            }
          ],
